main event: Multiple objects were observed traveling in different directions towards the Northeast over New York, New York on September 15, 1965.
interesting points: The objects were white in color and were likely reflecting light from the New York World's Fair.
The observer could not definitely identify the objects behind buildings.
The objects were observed for about 30 seconds.
No physical evidence or photographs were obtained.
The conclusion was that the objects were likely caused by reflecting light formations at the New York World's Fair.
result: Possible Reflecting light from N. Y. World's Fair
